        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/prainua">@prainua</a>,</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="prainua" data-post="3" data-topic="1762">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://community.frontity.org/user_avatar/community.frontity.org/prainua/40/1002_2.png" class="avatar"> prainua:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>and how clean up head ?)</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>What do you mean by that? What are you trying to achieve?</p>
<p>The <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/api-reference-1/frontity-head-tags">@frontity/head-tags</a> package in combination with <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/rest-api-head-tags/">REST API – Head Tags</a> WordPress plugin allows you to directly add to your HTML the header tags defined in your WP installation</p>
<p>You can find more info about this here → <a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/frontity-release-rest-api-head-tags-plugin-and-package/1069">Frontity release: REST API - Head Tags plugin and package</a></p>
<p>What do you plan to build with Frontity?</p>
