      <item>
        <title>Error when install head-tags</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[juanma]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Hi <a class="mention" href="https://community.frontity.org/u/prainua">@prainua</a>,</p>
<p>Please try the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Verify that you’re executing <code>npm install @frontity/head-tags</code> from the root of a frontity project</p>
<ul>
<li>Is your  <code>mac-plasty</code> folder a frontity project (I mean, the result of <code>npx frontity create mac-plasty</code> <a href="https://docs.frontity.org/learning-frontity/project">which is a folder containing a <code>frontity.settings.js</code></a>) ?</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>If you’re getting this error from your root of your frontity project then you have a permissions issue related to NPM. This can be provoked for several reasons depending on the user you’re logged in, the permissions set in that folder, and so on (search in Google for: <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=npm+install+missing+write+access"><em>npm install missing write access</em></a> or <a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=npm+install+ENOENT"><em>npm install ENOENT</em></a></p>
<ul>
<li>
<img src="https://community.frontity.org/images/emoji/apple/point_right.png?v=9" title=":point_right:" class="emoji" alt=":point_right:"> Most of the cases these permissions issues can be solved by doing (from the root of your frontity project) → <code>rm -rf node_modules &amp;&amp; rm -rf package-lock.json &amp;&amp; npm install</code>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Let us know how it goes</p>
<p>What do you plan to build with Frontity?</p>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/error-when-install-head-tags/1762/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
        <link>https://community.frontity.org/t/error-when-install-head-tags/1762/2</link>
